<tal:block metal:use-macro="layout" i18n:domain="dbas" metal:define-macro="layout">
  <tal:block metal:fill-slot="content_page">

    <section>
      <div class="text-center big-header">
        <h3 class="text-center">
          <span i18n:translate="field_experiment_2017">Field Experiment 2017</span>
        </h3>
        <p i18n:translate="most_important_information_about_field_experiment" class="lead text-center">
          Most important information about our field experiment in May 2017
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <div class="wrapper-container">

      <div class="container colored-container">
        <div class="row" style="margin: 1em">
          <div class="col-md-12">
            <div class="row" style="margin-bottom: 1em">
              <p class="col-md-2 lead" style="margin-bottom: 0" i18n:translate="when_where">When/Where?</p>
              <div class=" col-md-10"><span i18n:translate="may_2017_hhu">May 2017 at the University of DÃ¼sseldorf, Germany.</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="row" style="margin-bottom: 1em">
              <p class="col-md-2 lead" style="margin-bottom: 0" i18n:translate="setting">Setting?</p>
              <div class="col-md-10">
                <span i18n:translate="setting_description">We invited all computer science students of our university via mail to talk about the question: How can the studies of computer-science be improved and the problems caused by the large number of students be solved?</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="row" style="margin-bottom: 1em">
              <p class="col-md-2 lead" style="margin-bottom: 0" i18n:translate="key_fact">Key Facts?</p>
              <div class="col-md-10">
                <span i18n:translate="key_facts">Our key facts in short</span>:
                <ul>
                  <li><span i18n:translate="key_fact1">318 visitor, 137 returned at least once</span></li>
                  <li><span i18n:translate="key_fact2">47 registrations, 35 contributed at least once</span></li>
                  <li><span i18n:translate="key_fact3">235 contributed arguments</span></li>
                  <li><span i18n:translate="key_fact4">47 flagged statements</span></li>
                </ul>
                <span i18n:translate="discussion_can_be_seen">The discussion can be seen</span>
                <a href="${request.application_url}/discuss/verbesserung-des-informatik-studiengangs"
                   target="_blank" i18n:translate="here">here</a>
                <span i18n:translate="and_a_translated">and a translated, english version is available</span>
                <a target="_blank"
                   href="${request.application_url}/discuss/improve-the-course-of-computer-science-studies" i18n:translate="here">here</a>.
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="row" style="margin-bottom: 1em">
              <p class="col-md-2 lead" style="margin-bottom: 0" i18n:translate="why">Why?</p>
              <div class="col-md-10">
                <span i18n:translate="key_questions">We were primarily focused on two question</span>:
                <ul>
                  <li i18n:translate="key_question1">
                    Does the dialog-based approach works for untrained users in a real-world setting?
                  </li>
                  <li i18n:translate="key_question2">
                    Does a decentralized moderation system works for a dialog-based argumentation system?
                  </li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="row" style="margin-bottom: 1em">
              <p class="col-md-2 lead" style="margin-bottom: 0" i18n:translate="findings">Findings?</p>
              <div class="col-md-10">
                <span i18n:translate="findings1">We had many findings from our field experiment. The main results are summarized in</span>
                <a href="https://www.researchgate.net/publication/320065783_Dialog-Based_Online_Argumentation_Findings_from_a_Field_Experiment"
                   target="_blank" i18n:translate="this_paper">this paper</a>.
                <span i18n:translate="findings2">Next to this, our colleague developed a tool to translate real world argumentation of D-BAS into abstract argumentation frameworks. This paper can be read</span>
                <a href="http://ceur-ws.org/Vol-2012/AI3-2017_paper_11.pdf" i18n:translate="here">here</a>.
                <br>
                <span i18n:translate="findings3">The resulting dump of our PostgreSQL database can be downloaded from our</span>
                <a href="${request.application_url}/static/data/fieldtest_05_2017.tar.bz2" i18n:translate="server">server</a>
                (<span i18n:translate="license_cc_by_nc_sa">License CC BY-NC-SA</span>).
                <span i18n:translate="the archive contains">The archive contains three versions: the originaldataset of the discussion in German, a dataset which includes some corrections and a translated one.</span>
                <span i18n:translate="findings4">The translation into an abstract AF can be</span>
                <a href="${request.application_url}/static/data/fieldtest_05_2017.apx" i18n:translate="fetched to">
                  fetched to
                </a>.
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="row" style="margin-bottom: 0">
              <p class="col-md-2 lead" style="margin-bottom: 0" i18n:translate="ope-Source">Open Source?</p>
              <div class="col-md-10">
                <span i18n:translate="of_course_it_is_open_source">Of course! Every used tool is published under the MIT licence and hosted on GitHub</span>:
                <ul>
                  <li>
                    <a href="https://github.com/hhucn/dbas" target="_blank">
                      D-BAS: The Dialog-Based Argumentation System
                    </a>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <a href="https://github.com/hhucn/discuss" target="_blank">
                      discuss: Embedding dialog-based discussions into arbitrary web-contexts
                    </a>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <a href="https://github.com/hhucn/dabasco" target="_blank">
                      dabasco: Putting the spice into D-BAS
                    </a>
                  </li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

  </tal:block>
</tal:block>